deck: Melinda May is a level 7 S.H.I.E.L.D. agent, nicknamed "The Cavalry". She's a veteran pilot and soldier with many years of experience. She withdrew from the duty as a field agent after an incident in Manama, Bahrain which left her slightly damaged. However, Melinda returned to the field when Agent Phil Coulson recruited her onto his team.
description:
Creation

The character originated in the Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. television series, and like the other characters, was not an existing comic character. After becoming a fan favorite, Melinda May was brought into the mainstream Earth-616 comic canon by writer Mark Waid.

The character was initially conceived as a white woman named Althea Rice, but was heavily rewritten on the strength of Ming-Na Wen's audition.

Other Media

Live Action

Marvel´s Agents of Shield

In the Marvel Cinematic Universe, Melinda May is introduced as a legendary S.H.I.E.L.D. agent recruited by Phil Coulson as part of his team. She has a dark and mysterious past, and was left traumatized after an experience where she was forced to kill a number of cultists during a mission. As a result, she is hesitant to get into field work again, and initially agrees to Coulson's offer on the condition that she only act as the team's pilot.

Melinda quickly moves back into active field work, and enters into a sexual relationship with Grant Ward. She also develops a mother/daughter relationship with Skye, whom she grows very protective of. In the season finale, she defeats Ward after he is revealed to be a double agent working for HYDRA.

In the series, she is portrayed by Ming-Na Wen.

Games

Marvel Future Fight

Melinda May is a non-playable character in the game.

deck: A brilliant but socially awkward engineer and Jemma Simmons' research partner.
description:
Other Media

Television

Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.

Born in Scotland Leopold Fitz is genius-level engineer. He attended the S.H.I.E.L.D. Academy of Science and Technology along with bio-chem expert Jemma Simmons, with whom he developed a strong friendship. Among their instructors at the academy were Professor Vaughn and chemical kinetics advisor, Professor Franklin Hall.

After graduating from the academy, Fitz was happy to spend all of his time in a lab, but at the urging of Simmons the pair put in for a field position. They were recruited by Agent Phil Coulson to be the science crew for a new team he was putting together. Stationed on the Bus, the pair has designed specialized equipment and compounds on the fly in emergency situations.

During their first foray into the field Fitz developed the Night-Night Gun, a hi-tech tranquilizer gun which delivers a tiny amount of dendrotoxin. This was later used in the mission to incapacitate Mike Peterson, who was about to explode due to experimentation by the Centipede Group. On another mission when the team was investigating a 0-8-4, Peruvian rebels took over of the Bus; Fitz used his D.W.A.R.F.s to activate the old HYDRA weapon in order to regain control of the Bus.

Sometime later, Fitz and Agent Grant Ward were assigned by Agent Victoria Hand to infiltrate the border of South Ossetia and destroy an enemy weapon known as the "Overkill Device". Despite his inexperience, Fitz showed quick thinking, ingenuity and courage during the assignment and was essential to the successful completion of the mission. Agent Fitz' noteworthy actions include the timely activation of a Localized EMP Device when his and Agent Ward's lives were in jeopardy, gaining the trust of the locals and the modification of the Overkill Device's core, which allowed him to neutralize the enemy soldiers weapons.

Fitz was again forced out of his niche when the team got separated during a mission in Italy while pursuing a Cybertek shipment for Ian Quinn, leaving only him and Skye to continue the chase. After he sent a tracking beacon, Fitz waited for the others while Skye went inside Quinn's mansion where was shot twice in the stomach. In an attempt to save Skye’s life Coulson gave Fitz and Simmons access to files on his resurrection. Fitz managed figured out the location of the Guest House facility and went with Coulson, Ward and Agent John Garrett, who had temporarily joined the team, to find an experimental drug called GH-325. Entering the facility the group eliminated the two guards only to find the place rigged with explosives. Fitz managed to find the drug and get out before the facility implodes, returning to the Bus they administer the drug to Skye, successfully saving her. Unfortunately, that was the only sample he retrieved, so Fitz and Simmons took blood samples from Skye in hopes of duplicating the miracle drug.

After calling in several agents the team was able to locate Mike Peterson, now calling himself Deathlok, and track him back to the Clairvoyant. Converging on new location they briefly encounter Deathlok again, but he flees into the sewers. They soon find Thomas Nash, a vegetative man on life support who must speak through a computer claiming to be the Clairvoyant. Nash says that Centipede will kill Skye, prompting Ward to shoot him. When Simmons was called to the Hub to be a consultant on Deathlok, Fitz put in a secret phone line so that they could secretly discuss her findings on GH-325. However, he found that Melinda May already had one. Telling Skye about this, the two realize that the Clairvoyant was not Nash and must be a S.H.I.E.L.D. agent. Finding that the two had discovered her line May chased down Fitz hoping to incapacitate him with an I.C.E.R. before he could reveal her secret to Coulson, but hanged m locked himself in the lab before she got him. Coulson and Skye arrive beginning a standoff with May in the Bus's hangar. Coulson accuses her of being a traitor, but before May can explain the Bus is remotely hijacked by Victoria Hand. This gives Coulson an opening; tranquilizing May he locks her in interrogation with Ward. After Garrett rejoins the team when his jet is attacked by S.H.I.E.L.D. drones, Skye deciphers an encoded message on the S.H.I.E.L.D. revealing HYDRA's infiltration of the organization. When they reached the Hub, the team uses Fitz's invention, the Mouse Hole, to avoid capture. Believing Hand to be the real Clairvoyant, the group splits into teams to capture her and rescue Simmons. Coulson, May, Garrett and Fitz manage to capture a computer room in the Hub, but while talking with Coulson, Garrett accidentally outs himself as the true Clairvoyant, which greatly upsetting Fitz. Garrett offers him a place in HYDRA, an offer which Fitz rejects. In the ensuing battle, Coulson and May manage to kill the HYDRA agents and capture Garrett.

When the Hub is compromised the team, sans Ward and now joined by Antoine Triplett, head go to a secret S.H.I.E.L.D. base called Providence in the Canadian wilderness. Enroute Fitz began to notice the attraction that Simmons had for Triplett, whom Fitz distrusted since he had worked under Garrett.

Fitz went with Phil Coulson, Triplett and Simmons to Portland to apprehend Marcus Daniels, an escapee from the Fridge with energy absorption powers. When he discovered Coulson's past relationship with Audrey Nathan and Daniels, he talked Coulson into using her as bait. Fitz modified stage lights using to emit gamma rays which overloaded Marcus’ powers causing him to explode. When the group returned to Providence, they found the Bus and the other half of the team gone. While looking for a skillet to help Simmons make pancakes, Fitz finds a message left by Skye, "Ward is HYDRA," just as Simmons found Agent Eric Koenig's body. When Simmons' autopsy report proved Ward was the killer, Fitz snaps and has to be calmed by Coulson. Providence is then assaulted by Colonel Talbot and his troops, having been led there by Maria Hill. Talbot demands that the team turn themselves in, but Coulson manages to convince Hill to help him and they escape, heading to California where they rescue Skye.

Eventually, the team locates John Garrett and Grant Ward in Havana, Cuba. While the rest of the team raids the HYDRA base, Fitz and Simmons spy on the Centipede Project as they prepare to relocate. However, the two are captured by Ward and brought to Garrett aboard the Bus. There Fitz activated an EMP Joy Buzzer that shorted out Garrett's cybernetics, fatally injuring him. Fitz begged Ward to let him die, but Garrett told Ward to kill Fitz. Putting the two in a Medical Pod, Ward ejected them off the Bus into the Atlantic Ocean. Now trapped with Simmons on the seabed 90 feet down, Fitz jury-rigged a beacon transmitting a distress signal on an unmonitored S.H.I.E.L.D. frequency, all with a broken arm. When Simmons woke up, he explained the situation to her; there was no way out of the container, and they were going to die. However, Simmons eventually devised a way to break the glass keeping out the water. With some hope of escape, the pair worked the problem further. Eventually, with the detonation ready to go, Fitz handed Simmons a one-time use air supply and explained that there wouldn't be enough for the both of them. After a tearful display of affection from Simmons, Fitz triggers the explosion. Not willing to give up her closest friend, Simmons dragged Fitz with her to the surface where they were rescued by the timely arrival of Nick Fury, responding to their makeshift distress signal. While Simmons was placed in a Hyperbaric Chamber to recover from the pressure sickness, Fitz was examined by a medical team. His brain went without oxygen for an extended period of time, although his heart was still beating. Fitz ultimately survived the ordeal. However, when asked about him later, the fully recovered Simmons would only say "he's alive" with no further context, implying that Fitz suffered brain damage from oxygen deprivation.

deck: Grant Ward was a HYDRA infiltrator in S.H.I.E.L.D. disguised as a level 7 agent. Trained by John Garret to become a cold-blooded killer, he was more loyal to him than to HYDRA. As an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D., he was recruited onto Agent Coulson's team, though eventually broke cover and returned to Hydra.
description:
Battleworld

Grant Ward appeared as an agent of the HYDRA empire. He talked to Arnim Zola about the fate of an other Hydra agent.

Other Media

Television

Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.

Grant Ward grew up in the Massachusetts area. His childhood was less than ideal, his older brother Christian was abusive and would frequently force Ward to beat up his younger brother. One incident in particular Maynard threw his younger brother into a well and wouldn't allow Ward to rescue him, though Ward eventually managed to do it without his brother knowing.

In 1999, Ward set fire to his parents' house not knowing that his older brother Maynard was inside at the time. Maynard survived the blaze and pushed for Grant to be tried as an adult. While at a juvenile detention center, Ward was approached by John Garrett of S.H.I.E.L.D., who offered him a choice - leave with him now and be taught the skills needed to survive or face prison. Ward agreed, and for five years Garrett trained him, teaching him self-sufficiency by spending months out in the wilderness with no one but a dog named Buddy for company. Eventually, Garrett revealed his allegiance to HYDRA and had Ward implanted in S.H.I.E.L.D. as a sleeper agent.

When Phil Coulson assembled a new team of specialists to investigate new, strange and unknown threats, Garrett suggested to Coulson that Ward be a part of his new team, in order to "smooth out" Ward's "rough edges", but in reality, Ward was to be Garrett's undercover asset to try to discover the truth of Coulson's resurrection.

During the team's first mission together, they encountered a Rising Tide "hacktivist" known only as Skye, who was their only lead in finding Mike Peterson, a man who exhibited superhuman abilities. Ward took an instant dislike to Skye, having had a negative experience with the Rising Tide after their release of classified data during ongoing operations, he also saw her as an unknown factor that neither Ward nor Garrett had calculated. After the mission, Phil Coulson recruited her to the team as a consultant, despite Ward's objections. However, after Skye's quick thinking saved his life while taking back the Bus from Peruvian hijackers, Ward saw a way to learn more about her, thus removing any unknown element she might bring into the mix. Ward agreed to be her "Supervising Officer" and oversee her training and education. Ward began Skye's training but felt that she wasn't fully committing herself to it or to S.H.I.E.L.D., so Coulson suggested a different, more personal approach. Ward responded by giving some details of his personal life and rough childhood to Skye, describing his so-called "defining moment" to her.

During the operation to rescue Dr. Franklin Hall in Malta, Ward objected when Skye volunteered to infiltrate the compound of Ian Quinn, stating that she wasn't nearly qualified. Despite his doubts Skye was able to complete her mission, allowing Ward and Coulson to infiltrate the compound. Afterwards, Skye seemed to fully commit herself to her training and S.H.I.E.L.D. However, a few weeks later, Skye seemingly betrayed the team by Skye, by alerting her former boyfriend, hacker Miles Lydon, that S.H.I.E.L.D. was closing in on him while tracking down a leak concerning Chan Ho Yin, a pyrokinetic living in Hong Kong. Ward discovered the two and took them into custody aboard the Bus. When Ward produced evidence that Lydon had accepted payment of one million dollars for the information that endangered Chan's life, Skye was infuriated and felt betrayed by Lydon. Later, during the operation to extract Chan from Project Centipede Ward released Skye, needing her help to rescue Coulson and Melinda May. Skye managed to hack Centipede's mainframe and release the locked doors, allowing Coulson and May to escape. Coulson later agreed to let Skye remain on the team as long as she came completely clean with the team and agreed to wear a Tracking Bracelet at all times.

Ward further gained the trust of the team by jumping out of the Bus to rescue Jemma Simmons, who had jumped from the Bus without a parachute in order to protect her team from a Chitauri Virus. Ward was never in any danger as he had a parachute and administered the cure to Simmons during free-fall. He also bonded with teammate Leo Fitz, when Agent Victoria Hand assigned the two to a mission in Georgia to destroy an enemy weapon known as the "Overkill Device".

After the events of Thor: Dark World, Ward along with the rest of the team proceeded to clean up the mess the battle had left in Greenwich. However, the clean up was interrupted as they were called to investigate an ancient Asgardian weapon known as the Berserker Staff, part of which had been discovered by pagan hate group, lead by Jakob Nystrom and Petra Larsen. With the assistance of a professor in Spain named Dr. Elliot Randolph the team is able to discover the location of the second piece. While retrieving the staff section, Ward touches the staff and relives a traumatic childhood memory involving his abusive brother and a well. He becomes irritable, aggressive, and possesses increased strength. The team discovers that Randolph is actually an Asgardian who has lived on Earth for centuries, and he gives them the location of the third staff piece. The team arrives, but are confronted pagans who had beaten them to the location. Seeing no other choice, Grant reassembles the Staff and, with the help of May, defeat the group. Later, Ward declines Skye's invitation to having a chat and follows Agent May into her room instead, seeing her as the biggest threat to his mission, he allowed things to get intimate.

Following a led on the Clairvoyant, the team board a train in Italy where they split into groups, with Ward undercover as a train conductor in order to track down package being shipped to Ian Quinn. However, the security team catches on causing Coulson and Ward to jump off the train, which mysteriously disappears afterward. Meeting back up with May at the "Bus", the three are able to locate the train and Simmons, but Fitz and Skye are gone. They track them to Quinn's compound and raid it, arresting Quinn. However, they discover Skye near death. Simmons trying to help, but can only sustain her temporarily by placing her into a hyperbaric chamber. Coulson and the team rush Skye to a S.H.I.E.L.D. medical facility to save her life. However, the doctors are only able to stabilize her, forcing Coulson to bring her to the same location where he was revived. Joined by agents John Garrett and Antoine Triplett, the team travels to the "Guest House" to recover GH-325, the miracle drug used to revive Coulson. Coulson, Ward, Garrett and Fitz enter the facility and eliminate the two guards there only to find the place rigged with explosives. They manage to recover the drug and get out before the facility implodes, returning to the "Bus" they administer the drug to Skye, successfully saving her.

The team is summoned to investigate an energy reading from the Bifrost, where they encounter Lady Sif, She explains she is tracking Lorelei, an Asgardian sorceress with power to control the minds of men. They team trace Lorelei to a biker bar where they fight her men, but Lorelei enchants Ward and escapes with him to Las Vegas. After spending the night together, Ward reveals his feelings toward Skye and May to Lorelei and tells her that Coulson's team stood between her and world domination. Together, they hijacked the Bus, eluding Coulson, Sif, and a S.H.I.E.L.D. team, and commandeer the "Bus". Lorelei encounters May and reveals that Ward’s heart is with someone else. Sif confronts Lorelei while May fights Ward. Sif fixes the collar to Lorelei’s neck, undoing her enchantment, and returns Lorelei to Asgard. May ends her relationship with Ward.

Agents Garrett, Triplett, Hand, Sitwell, and Blake join the team to hunt for the Clairvoyant. The agents pair up to pursue different Clairvoyant candidates. Ward was teamed with Triplett to investigate Elijah Fordham, but before they could find him, they were called to help May and Blake against Mike Peterson, now calling himself Deathlok. Concluding that Thomas Nash is the Clairvoyant because of Deathlok's presence, the team converges on his new location where they briefly encounter him again, but he flees into the sewers. Nevertheless, they find Nash, a vegetative man on life support who must speak through a computer. When Nash boasts about being the Clairvoyant and says that Centipede will kill Skye, Ward shoots him. Afterwards, Ward is taken into custody and locked in interrogation on board the "Bus".

However, after Skye deciphers a secret code on S.H.I.E.L.D.'s network revealing HYDRA's infiltration, Coulson releases Ward. When the Bus arrives at the Hub, the group splits into teams to capture Victoria Hand, whom they believe is the Clairvoyant. Skye and Grant Ward team up heading to the central computer to plant a bomb, while the rest of the team went to get Simmons and Triplett. During this time, Skye and Ward admitted their mutual attraction, but Skye chooses not to pursue any relationship. After Garrett reveals himself as the true Clairvoyant, and is captured by Coulson and May, Ward volunteers to accompany Hand to the Fridge to Garrett's imprisonment personally. Once airborne, Hand offers Ward the chance to execute Garrett to atone for killing Nash by mistake. Instead, Ward kills Hand and her agents, freeing Garrett and revealing his own allegiance to HYDRA.

Ward is next seen freeing Raina, taking her to Garrett's base of operation in Havana, Cuba where she is presented with drugs taken from the Guest House and an encrypted hard drive contain all of Team Coulson's data so that she could perfect Project Deathlok.. Afterwards, Ward and Garret along with several other HYDRA agents raid the Fridge, releasing its prisoners, including Blackout and Ian Quinn, and obtaining its confiscated weapons, including the Berserker Staff, the Peruvian 0-8-4, and the Gravitonium. However, when Raina reported that only Skye could decrypt the hard drive, Garrett order Ward to return to Coulson's team to get the pass codes from her.

Arriving at the secret S.H.I.E.L.D. base, Providence, Ward lied to the team about the Fridge, telling them that he killed Garrett as he freed the prisoners. Coulson decided to take half the team to Portland, Oregon to pursue Blackout, but Agent Eric Koenig insisted that first they all be properly vetted; a process which Ward only just passed. When Skye and Koenig discuss using NSA satellites to watch the prison break, Ward knew it would expose him as HYDRA. Killing Koenig, Ward hid his body in a closet, and convinced Skye to leave with him on the Bus. Unknown to Ward, however, Skye had already found Koenig's body and left the message "Ward is HYDRA" for her teammates to find. The head to LA, since the encryption was location-based. While there, Skye tried to escape, but Deathlok apprehended her. When Ward fails to convince her to decrypt the drive, Deathlok shoots him with a device that induced a heart attack. He gives Skye the ultimatum: decrypt the hard drive, or Ward dies. After try to reason with him and failing she relented and Deathlok stops Wards heart attack. With the hard drive decrypted Ward prepares the Bus for take-off, but is confronted by Maria Hill, distracting him long enough for Coulson to board and rescue Skye. Ward begins to pursue, but Deathlok informs him that they had recalled them to the base in Cuba by Garrett. Now with access to the hard drive Raina manages to recreate GH-325.

When Garrett ordered the abandonment of the base for the new Cybertek Manufacturing Facility, Ward discovered Leo Fitz and Jemma Simmons spying on them. Capturing them he brings them to Garrett aboard the Bus, where Fitz activated an EMP Joy Buzzer, further damaging Garrett, who was already suffering from organ failure. Ward ejected them in a storage pod from the Bus into the Atlantic Ocean. When he returned to Garrett, Ward learned that in order to save his life Raina had injected him with the GH-325. However, when Garrett became increasingly erratic because of the drug, Ward became worried about the state of his mind. When Coulson and his team broke into the facility, he was tasked with apprehending Skye but was stopped by Melinda May with whom he engaged in a long battle that ended with his foot nailed to the floor, several bruises, and a fractured larynx. He was later imprisoned by U.S. Marines.

Three months later Ward is a prisoner in the Playground, Coulson's new base of operations. He was bought there in the hopes they could get HYDRA intel off him, but he refused to speak to anyone except Skye. After an encounter with superhuman Carl Creel, Coulson sends Skye to question Ward about his connection with John Garrett and HYDRA. Upon her arrival at his cell, Ward begins to tell her about his multiple suicide attempts. Skye threatens to leave, but Ward gives in, telling her how HYDRA had been communicating. Before she left Ward tried to tell her about her father, but she cut him off returning him to isolation.
